"```sql\nSELECT Patient.ID, \n       YEAR(CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - YEAR(Patient.Birthday) AS age\nFROM Patient\nJOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE Laboratory.LDH BETWEEN 600 AND 800;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the ID and calculated age of patients whose lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) levels are between 600 and 800, which is considered above the normal range according to the provided evidence. The age is calculated by subtracting the birth year from the current year. The query joins the `Patient` and `Laboratory` tables using the `ID` as the foreign key."